# Basic Store Creation

Zustand uses create() to define stores as hooks.

```typescript
import { create } from 'zustand';

interface BearState {
  bears: number;
  increase: (by: number) => void;
  reset: () => void;
}

const useBearStore = create<BearState>()((set) => ({
  bears: 0,
  increase: (by) => set((state) => ({ bears: state.bears + by })),
  reset: () => set({ bears: 0 }),
}));

// Usage in component
function BearCounter() {
  const bears = useBearStore((state) => state.bears);
  const increase = useBearStore((state) => state.increase);
  return <button onClick={() => increase(1)}>{bears} bears</button>;
}
```

Selectors prevent unnecessary re-renders. Only subscribe to what you need.

**Category:** Core
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/getting-started/introduction

# Slices Pattern with DevTools

Split large stores into slices for maintainability.

```typescript
import { create, StateCreator } from 'zustand';
import { devtools } from 'zustand/middleware';

type BearSlice = { bears: number; addBear: () => void };
type FishSlice = { fishes: number; addFish: () => void };
type JungleStore = BearSlice & FishSlice;

const createBearSlice: StateCreator<
  JungleStore, [['zustand/devtools', never]], [], BearSlice
> = (set) => ({
  bears: 0,
  addBear: () => set((state) => ({ bears: state.bears + 1 }), undefined, 'bear/addBear'),
});

const createFishSlice: StateCreator<
  JungleStore, [['zustand/devtools', never]], [], FishSlice
> = (set) => ({
  fishes: 0,
  addFish: () => set((state) => ({ fishes: state.fishes + 1 }), undefined, 'fish/addFish'),
});

const useJungleStore = create<JungleStore>()(
  devtools((...args) => ({
    ...createBearSlice(...args),
    ...createFishSlice(...args),
  }))
);
```

The 3rd argument to set() names the action in Redux DevTools.

**Category:** Patterns
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/middlewares/devtools

# Persist Middleware

Automatically save and restore store state.

```typescript
import { create } from 'zustand';
import { persist, createJSONStorage } from 'zustand/middleware';

type BearStore = { bears: number; addABear: () => void };

export const useBearStore = create<BearStore>()(
  persist(
    (set, get) => ({
      bears: 0,
      addABear: () => set({ bears: get().bears + 1 }),
    }),
    {
      name: 'food-storage',
      storage: createJSONStorage(() => sessionStorage),
    }
  )
);
```

Options: name (required, storage key), storage (default localStorage), partialize (select which state to persist), version + migrate (schema migration), onRehydrateStorage (callback).

**Category:** Middleware
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/integrations/persisting-store-data

# Immer Middleware

Write mutable-looking code that produces immutable updates.

```typescript
import { create } from 'zustand';
import { immer } from 'zustand/middleware/immer';

type State = { count: number };
type Actions = {
  increment: (qty: number) => void;
  decrement: (qty: number) => void;
};

export const useCountStore = create<State & Actions>()(
  immer((set) => ({
    count: 0,
    increment: (qty) => set((state) => { state.count += qty; }),
    decrement: (qty) => set((state) => { state.count -= qty; }),
  }))
);
```

Requires: `npm install immer`

**Category:** Middleware
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/integrations/immer-middleware

# Combining Middlewares

Stack devtools + persist for debugging + persistence.

```typescript
import { create } from 'zustand';
import { devtools, persist } from 'zustand/middleware';

interface BearState {
  bears: number;
  increase: (by: number) => void;
}

const useBearStore = create<BearState>()(
  devtools(
    persist(
      (set) => ({
        bears: 0,
        increase: (by) => set((state) => ({ bears: state.bears + by })),
      }),
      { name: 'bearStore' }
    )
  )
);
```

Middleware order: outermost applied first. devtools(persist(...)) means devtools wraps persist.

Available middlewares: devtools, persist, immer, subscribeWithSelector, combine.

**Category:** TypeScript
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/guides/advanced-typescript

# subscribeWithSelector Middleware

Subscribe to specific state slices outside React components.

```typescript
import {createStore} from 'zustand/vanilla';
import {subscribeWithSelector} from 'zustand/middleware';
import {shallow} from 'zustand/shallow';

const store = createStore<State>()(subscribeWithSelector((set) => ({
  count: 0,
  name: 'Guest',
  increment: () => set(s => ({count: s.count + 1}))
})));

// Subscribe to count only
const unsub1 = store.subscribe(state => state.count, (count, prev) => {
  console.log(prev, '->', count);
});

// With custom equality function
const unsub2 = store.subscribe(state => state.name, (name) => {
  console.log(name);
}, {equalityFn: (a,b) => a===b, fireImmediately: true});

// Multiple values with shallow equality
const unsub3 = store.subscribe(
  state => [state.count, state.name],
  ([c,n]) => console.log(c,n),
  {equalityFn: shallow}
);
```

Useful for non-React contexts: event handlers, WebSocket callbacks, middleware, Node.js code. fireImmediately: true fires callback immediately with current state.

**Category:** Middleware
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/middlewares/subscribe-with-selector

# Outside React

Access and modify state from non-React code.

```jsx
const useDogStore = create(() => ({
  paw: true,
  snout: true,
  fur: true
}));

// Get current state (non-reactive)
const paw = useDogStore.getState().paw;

// Update state from anywhere
useDogStore.setState({paw: false});

// Subscribe to all changes
const unsub = useDogStore.subscribe(console.log);
unsub(); // cleanup
```

Useful for: event handlers, WebSocket callbacks, timers, middleware, Node.js code.

getState() returns current state synchronously. setState() updates state without component subscription. subscribe() listens to all state changes.

**Category:** Core
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/getting-started/introduction

# Next.js SSR Store Factory

Create store instances per-request to prevent state leakage.

```typescript
import {createStore} from 'zustand/vanilla';

export type CounterState = {count: number};
export type CounterActions = {increment: () => void; decrement: () => void};
export type CounterStore = CounterState & CounterActions;

export const defaultInitState: CounterState = {count: 0};

export const createCounterStore = (initState = defaultInitState) => {
  return createStore<CounterStore>()((set) => ({
    ...initState,
    increment: () => set(s => ({count: s.count + 1})),
    decrement: () => set(s => ({count: s.count - 1})),
  }));
};
```

Use createStore (vanilla) not create (React) for SSR. Each request gets its own store instance to prevent state leakage between requests. Wrap with React context provider for component access.

Pattern: useCounterStore hook factory wraps createCounterStore.

**Category:** Patterns
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/guides/nextjs

# Testing - Mock Store Auto-Reset

Mock zustand with auto-reset per test.

```typescript
// __mocks__/zustand.ts
import {act} from '@testing-library/react';
import type * as Z from 'zustand';

export * from 'zustand';

const {create: actualCreate, createStore: actualCreateStore} = jest.requireActual<typeof Z>('zustand');

export const storeResetFns = new Set<() => void>();

const createUncurried = <T>(stateCreator: Z.StateCreator<T>) => {
  const store = actualCreate(stateCreator);
  const initialState = store.getInitialState();
  storeResetFns.add(() => store.setState(initialState, true));
  return store;
};

export const create = (<T>(sc: Z.StateCreator<T>) => 
  typeof sc === 'function' ? createUncurried(sc) : createUncurried
) as typeof Z.create;

afterEach(() => {
  act(() => {
    storeResetFns.forEach(fn => fn());
  });
});
```

For Vitest use vi.importActual instead of jest.requireActual. Captures initial state and resets all stores after each test automatically.

**Category:** Guide
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/guides/testing

# Reset State Pattern

Reset store to its initial state easily.

```typescript
const useSomeStore = create<State & Actions>()((set, get, store) => ({
  count: 0,
  name: 'Guest',
  reset: () => set(store.getInitialState()),
}));

// Usage
useSomeStore.getState().reset();
```

store.getInitialState() returns the exact state from when store was first created. Passing it to set() resets everything to that state.

Alternative: Manually specify reset action if getInitialState is not available.

**Category:** Patterns
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/guides/how-to-reset-state

# Triple Middleware Stack

Combine devtools + persist + immer for maximum functionality.

```typescript
import {create} from 'zustand';
import {devtools, persist} from 'zustand/middleware';
import {immer} from 'zustand/middleware/immer';
import type {} from '@redux-devtools/extension';

interface AppState {
  count: number;
  increment: () => void;
}

const useStore = create<AppState>()(
  devtools(
    persist(
      immer((set) => ({
        count: 0,
        increment: () => set((state) => { state.count += 1; }),
      })),
      {name: 'app-storage'}
    ),
    {name: 'AppStore'}
  )
);
```

Middleware order (outermost first): devtools wraps persist wraps immer. Each middleware adds capability: devtools (debugging), persist (localStorage), immer (mutable syntax). Requires: npm install immer. Type import for devtools: import type {} from '@redux-devtools/extension'.

**Category:** TypeScript
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/guides/advanced-typescript

# Persist with Hydration Control

Control when persisted state is loaded from storage.

```typescript
import {createStore} from 'zustand/vanilla';
import {persist} from 'zustand/middleware';

const store = createStore()(
  persist((set) => ({
    position: {x: 0, y: 0},
    setPosition: (p) => set({position: p})
  }), {
    name: 'position-storage',
    skipHydration: true,  // don't auto-load on creation
  })
);

// Manually rehydrate when ready (e.g., after DOM load)
setTimeout(() => {
  store.persist.rehydrate();
}, 2000);
```

skipHydration: true prevents automatic localStorage read on store creation. Call store.persist.rehydrate() when ready. Advanced options: onRehydrateStorage (callback before hydration), version + migrate (schema migration), partialize (select state to persist).

**Category:** Middleware
**URL:** https://zustand.docs.pmnd.rs/integrations/persisting-store-data
